content.detailedDescription: I was driving west on rt. 25 (tenney mt. hwy.), just before the plymouth/rumney town line.  to the north i noticed a light in the air that seemed to flicker.  then i noticed a craft which seemed dark and that only had a single light on it.  there were no normal navigational lights that you would find on an airplane.  object was travelling east.  these lights were just north of plymouth and rumney, east of stinson mt.  the second object that was travelling east was going as fast as a jet or perhaps as fast as a high-performance prop aircraft (400 knots plus).  i am reporting this because it seemed unusual to me.  it isn't every day you see a flickering light in the sky and then a craft which seems dark and with only a single light.  i am a little afraid of ufos so i didn't stick around to observe more.
content.summary: Noticed flying craft with no naviagation lights but with only single light.

content.detailedDescription:
1. my wife and i were sitting in backyard patio looking up at night sky
2. was a formation of 4-5 luminescent triangular objects traveling silently (no sound)and extremely rapidly northbound, one object was a bit "wobbly" - were not airplanes (we see commercial airtrafic at night on regular basis)
3. at first we were not sure what we were seeing, honestly i wondered if it was a flock of bird being lit from underneath gliding over us  - but they moved too fast and were not "flapping" and were more triangular than a bird or airplane
4. weird aerial events started at 11:50pm. it was a group of 4-5 objects triangular in shape all luminescent underneath (a hazy lit grey - solid - no blinking lites or anything in terms of coloration one sees on commercial air traffic). my wife and i had no idea what the objects were either but they were flying in formation - no doubt about that, one appeared to wobble badly then corrected itself in flight. both my wife and i agreed they were odd and "ufo" like.  we only caught site of them as they flew overhead rapidly heading from the south -northbound and we lost them in trees as they progressed. moments later as we moved to try to see into the distance we saw two more coming from the southeast heading northward. we continued to watch the skys and at 11:20pm i noticed a bright light (thought it was a star at first) rapidly move northbound (appeared to be much, much higher than the "triangles") it moved i called my wifes attention to it and we both saw it travel rapidly in a straight line from south to north disappearing from our view as it progressed across the sky. more strange aerial phenomenon continued - at aproximately 11:50am i noticed another star like light (again very high) this time travelling from the western part of the sky east, (much faster than the northbound one)again i called my wifes attention to it and it passed overhead and we lost it (our house obstucted us from viewing further as the object passed over it continuing eastward. the two "travelling stars" were traveling at a very high rate of speed - covering too much sky in too litle time to be an airplane (even one traveling near supersonic). from almost directly overhead until i lost it in the trees the northbound "traveling star" crossed sky until out of sight in about 20 - 30 seconds max, the other travelling eastbound was out of sight within 10 seconds easily. all objects were silent. the "traveling stars" were traveling in precise straight lines. finally at 12:05pm just before going into the house to say goodnight my wife and i both witnessed 2 more luminescent triangles flying in formation from the south east going northbound - this time they seemed to vanish just after we lost sight of them going past some treetops across the road. 
5. my wife is more of a skeptic than i am, she admits to seeing ufos but is not sure who/what those ufos were. i was excited and fascinated, she was more reserved and quite quiet about the whole thing.
6. objects passed into the horizon overtop trees and buildings - we lost sight of them then.

it was amazing to see some things frankly i never thought i would experience with my wife in my lifetime. but to see all the wierd aerial activity in one night was quite bizarre.

i'm deathly curious what ground radar reported (if you can find out).
content.summary: 4 luminescent triangles northbound, 2 more sighted twice, two other strange lights...

Sighting report:   this took place on march 10 1990 on a clear ski
night at 11 pm in gyumri, armenia. the object appeared to be about
200-300 yards high and its size was greater than the wingspan of 2
airbus planes. the object was metallic/dark and shaped like 2
saucers on top of each other. the top part was a little more dome
chaped and bottom more flat-like. its shape, although it was visible
even without the lights (moon-light), was "outlined" by lights and
there were additional lights on the bottom half of the disc that
were multicolored (projector-like). it had not cast a single light
in the direction of the land when i had seen it. it was a cold night
winter was just starting to end with snow and frost everywhere
still. this had happened only about a year and change after the
devastating earthquake in armenia, and i had heard from otherw who
had said they d seen ufo s in that area on different days. another
day (summer of that same year) people had reported seeing a ufo that
had hovered in the midst of the day in the air for a long time
(20-30 minutes)
the presence on the ufo that i had seen was very impressive and its
unmistakably un-earthly, non-human make was eminent.
after i had noticed it, it hovered in the air for perhaps 30 seconds
then took off in one direction and up, stopped for a second and took
off high into the air and became smaller than a star in seconds and
disappeared.
if you have questions please do not hesitate to contact me
content.summary: Dark metallic saucer over gyumri, armenia

content.detailedDescription:
Sighting report:   march 21st, 2005 @ 9:28pm at the corner of sam
mason rd. and route 11 my husband and i both witnessed a ufo above
the house at that intersection. it was mostly clear skies, some
clouds but not many. we were travelling north on rt. 11 towards our
turn onto sam mason, we were about 200 feet from our turn when i
first noticed it. it was similar to the air force stealth fighter
but without the points at the ends, there was flatness instead, and
also 3 times as large as a stealth fighter. it was hovering above
this house just above the treetops about 50 feet above the
roof.There were two lights on the underside of it ,one on each
"wing-tip", they were not blinking. the lights on our planes usually
blink. anyhow, as we drove closer, it rose higher and flew north
into the clouds, it disappeared within seconds. there was no engine
noise whatsoever. about a week or so later we saw a different ufo
also driving home. the time was 9:28pm. it was a red glowing light
that flew from east to west and then south effortlessly and within
seconds. we watched it until we couldn t see it anymore. we didn t
experience any "missing time" in either case.

Sighting report:   late last cummer or early fall, i went out to
 the end of the driveway to smoke a cigarette and look at the
 stars (which are plentiful in north-central wisconsin). my young
 sons came over to join me and to enjoy the evening. i happened
 to look over toward the house when i started to scream to the
 boys and point to an object moving from east to west over the
 house. it was an opaque flying object shaped somewhere betweem a
 triangle and a boomerang. when i per se, but you could see it
 move across the sky as it magnified the starfield in the
 background somewhat like what a magnifying glass would do if you
 laid it on a map an moved it around. although it is impossible
 to estimate it s size, i estimate as a referrence that it was
 the size of my thumb held out at arms length.

Sighting report:   on may 19th, around 3p.M., i was entering the
town that i live in and while i was turning to the first street on
my right, i spotted something shiny in the sky. it was sunny and few
clouds in the sky, i thought it was a plane but then i focused on
the object and i could tell that it was moving fast and there was no
wings like that of an airplane. i looked forward onto the road and
looked up few seconds later and could not spot it again. it was oval
and chrome to silver like color.

Sighting report:   on the morning of april 7th, 2005 i was camping
with my wife at the carrizo plains national mounument.  twenty
minutes before sunrise we were in our sleeping bags watching the
sunrise.  i noticed right above me a very bright star.  i know the
heavens well enough to know this was not a planet, but brighter than
jupiter which was setting to the west. it was also not on the
zenith, but directly above us.  i looked at it with my binoculars
and saw a faint zigzag line starting at the middle of the right hand
side and droping down to the left.  while alternating watching the
sunrise and star/planet like object we noticed a faint star moving
next to it.  that star moved erractedly from the north to the
northwest in comparison to the object.  we became very excited,
because this was not a shooting star or satalite.  we kept looking
at it and after about 10 minutes it was clear this object was moving
very slowly to the northeast.  we kept alternating watching the
sunrise and the object and the object did not lesson in it s
appearance even though the day was quite brightout by now. my last
look at the object was now 10-12 minutes after first noticing it.
after looking at the sunrise i looked up and it was not there!  i
then looked for it with my binoculars and saw a faint circular grey
spot where it was last seen and three sparkculing objects moving
southeast away from the grey spot.  there was no tracing marks or
sound, but the three objects faded after one minute.
i have seen satalites come into our atmosphere here in washington
and this was not like that at all.  it was circular like a planet
size object in the sky.  what did i see?

Sighting report:   daate: 04/07/2005
time: 8:40 p.M. 
location: buckingham county, virgina
2 miles south of buckingham baptist chuch on u.S. 15 north.
description: large octagonal shaped object (50 yard diameter
 approx.)flew over our car and over the highway 100-150  altitude
 as we traveled north.
the object had an octagonal outline that could be seen due to the
 large counter-clockwise pulsing lights that could be seen
 looking up at bottom of craft. there also was an intense white
 light that came from the crafts underside that shined toward the
 ground. the object made no noise whatsoever. green and yellow
 lights with slow counter-clockwise rotation underneath craft.
weather: 1/4 mile visibility with light rain.
other observations: cell phone interupted momentarily. i looked
 in the rear view mirror and it was gone. there were no street
 lights, cell phone towers or house lights observed anywhere in
 the immediate vicinity.

Sighting report:   at around 9:30 pm on 3/19/2005, i stepped
 outside my house to get some fresh air. i looked up, and to my
 surprise i saw a saucer-shaped craft with 4 lights, 2 of which
 blinked several colors, alternating between blue, purple, green,
 and red. the other two were white. the lights swirled around the
 side of the craft. i double checked to make sure it was not a
 tower of some sort, but at that time the only lights around were
 the yellow streetlights. another thing that conviced me it was a
 ufo was the "loooooooooooooooooo" sound it made as it streaked
 across the sky. definitely not something a man-made craft could
 have done, and i bet no man-made craft could have been as fast
 as this. it did not fly in a straight path, but curved, making a
 figure-eight of sorts. eventually, it faded out of view, and
 left just as quietly as it came.

i hope i was not hallucinating, but it seems my neighbors also
 spotted the object.

Sighting report:   during the late 1960 s i was a police officer
with northumbria constabulary and attached to the traffic
department. one night at approximetely 2 /2.30am, i was in company
with my sergeant and driving a patrol car along the a 108 tyne
tunnel road, heading towards the a1. at a point just past seaton
burn roundabout,i noted a glow coming from fields to my right - i
was unable to clarify the cause due to high enbankments either side
of the road. local knowkedge told me this being very much of a rural
location vehicular access was not an option. therefore, my intention
was to come off at the next slip road and double back towards the
illuminted area.
at this point an enormous ball of revolving flame rolled over the
top of the enbankment and came to rest on the opposite carriageway.
this  thing  for want of a better word, was revolving at high speed
and the only way i could quantify its appearence was comparing it to
two double deck buses tied together and alight.  the heat being
generated was unbelievable. even as a police officer panic began to
set in. nowhere in any training manual had i seen a procedure for
dealing with this type of occurrence.
accelerating away from the heat, my colleague attempeted to contact
our control room for assistance - unfortunately the radio was
inoperative due to heavy static.  as i pulled away, the object kept
pace with my vehicle, enough was enough, i was driving a
demonstration volvo 144s, fortunately fitted with air-conditioning,
a rarity in those days, and considered i could show a clean pair of
heels to this ball of fire. touching 110mph, i, as aware are that
what we were trying to escape had crossed the carriageway and was
positioned directly above our car at a height of 5 /6 feet. even
with the air-conditioning going full blast, we were starting to fry
and our persuer was edging closer to the roof of the patrol car.
within sight of the seaton burn roundbout/flyover, the area becomes
illuminated from the motorway lighting and traffic travelling along
the main highway which runs from edinburgh to london. we approached
the flyover at in excess of 80 mph before coming to a halt directly
over the dual carriageway.
getting out of the vehicle we noted the smell of burnt rubber coming
from the window and door seals which had suffered in the exptreme
heat. but what of the thing that had chased us? it was hovering
above a small copse of trees some 300yards distance, as if unsure
whether or not to continue. taking advantage of this situation, we
conacted our control room and reported the facts of the previous few
minutes. needless to say the response was one which generated every
joke about little green men and space ships. all very amusing until
the duty officer took over and told us, in no uncertain terms, that
we were to remain where we were and not drive the patrol car. his
tone of voice said it all - they thought we had been drinking!
just then, we heard a roar and on turning round say the blazing
object heading directly for us - we instinctively ducked and it
passed over our heads with inches to spare. it stopped, turned
towards the north and accelerated at an unbelievable speed,
disappearing in seconds. dazed and somewhat confused, we became
aware of the car radio churning out numerous reports by colleagues
of the object as it travelled across the northern part of the
county.
before long, the duty officer, rather sheepishly, advised us to
return to our base in wallsend and await instructions. this we
gladly did and were eventually told to take the rest of the shift
off.
the weather conditions were: fine and dry. there was a moon and
visability good

early next morning we and a number of fellow officers were required
to attend police headquarters where a number of senior officers were
also present. the purpose being for us to be interviewed by two very
high ranking air force officers. all very straightforward and
congenial. "thank you chaps for the information, very concise and
informative. might be better not to make too much of or say anything
about this incident, i sure you understand"!!!!
that was the end of things until a few months later when i had a
occasion to talk with one of my officers who had been present on the
evening in question. when asked what had been the outcome of the
investigation we understood to have been conducted, his response was
straightforward - the matter had been recorded as an official ufo
sighting.

i have two other sighting experiences, one as a police officer,
again in the northumberland area and the second, as a civillian, in
the suffolk area.

i hope this is of use to you.

Sighting report:   first sighting december 13th 1998
this was a crystal clear night and a craft passed over our window
twice along with a satelite travelling in a different trajectory but
at the same speed. the craft had an illuminated outer rim with four
large round white lights in a straight line underside. i will submit
an image that i have created as it is difficult to describe.
second sighting september 2000
this was a close encounter the craft passed across a valley and
directly over our heads. this craft was illuminated on all edges and
very large at around eight o clock in the evening with clear skys
and little wind. this craft was cubic and l-shaped as large as a
jumbo jet. it had a slight protrusion at the rear with three
balconies above. within the protrusion at the rear were mesh dishes
which were emitting a blue/purple light - this seemed to be
propelling the craft at around 40miles an hour (estimated).
underside the craft had three large white lights two at its tall end
and one at the other. these were joined by huge pipes. the craft was
so close we could see the bolts on the pipework. the craft emitted
an electrical humming noise which was not loud although it sounded
very powerfull. it is now five years on and i find myself asking are
they somewhere on dartmoor? are they still here? were they landing
or leaving? there are plenty of places on dartmoor to hide a craft
that size. my pictures are made with my computer so do not do
justice to the ufo s we have seen with our own eyes. i beleive we
have seen the future - imagine a world without the wheel.

Sighting report:   11/04/05@22.20and10/04/05around the same time me
and another family member saw a very large bright box in the sky
above a water treatment works in the local area i tried to take a
picture of the object at which point it went very dull and i could

Sighting report:   it was a wednessday, may 25th or may 18th, 2005
approximately 5 or 6pm. we were driving on 183 back to dallas from
fort worth. the sky was clear, blue with few white clouds.

i noticed a metalic sphere in the distant and my first thought was
it may be a ufo however the object did not move.   from the distance
i was at i would imagine something like an orange would cover up the
object from view at arms length.

i was trying to determine whether it was suspended in air or
attached to something, possibly a satellite dish or something like
that. however the object was clearly sphere shaped with nothing
sticking out of it or anything like that.

the next thing i thought of was possibly one of those balls you see
on telephone lines. i could not see any telephone lines to support
this theory. at this point i drove around towards the object but my
view was obstructed by trees and buildings as i turned onto a road
that looked as though it would take me closer. when my sight was no
longer obstructed i could not see the object anymore.

i did not report it because it wasn t "flying". it was either
hovering or suspended by something so i thought it was man made. but
the sighting has been bothering me for the past few weeks and i was
intruiged to find out if there were any reports around that time of
the same object.

thanks


ps what do you think about this prophet yahweh guy who supposedly
summons ufos?? how do you think it was done for the abc news
cameras?

Sighting report:   in 1960, i had enlisted in the ohio army national
guard and was sent to fort jackson, s.C to finih my advanced
infantry tactics school.  in the fall of 1960, our company was in
the open outdoors cleaning our equipment when someone noticed 3
cigar shaped objects in the sky overhead.  they were motionless and
yet they maintained an equal distance from each other.  they were to
the eyes, silver mettalic and solid forms. there was no blurring of
their outlines and according to our ""aircraft identifican" cards
indicated that if they b-52 bombers, they would be about 40-50
thousand feet above us.  two things that come to my mind that was
unusal, first, they remained overhead for so long that we returned
our weapons to the armory late that afternoon.  they became of no
further interest to usthat day.
secondly, the next morning at our company roll call formation, the
copany commander addressed us and told us that we "were not to talk
or discuss what we had seen" the day before, and if contacted by any
one about what we saw that we were to refer the person to the post
company commanding general. i have since looked for the sighting on
any program or listing of sightings, but have never found this
sighting.  in order for our company commander to tell us what he
did, the incident must have stirred up interest in areas other than
fort jackson.
if you have information about this sighting, i d really like to hear
from you.

Sighting report:   while attached to the 2ndbn 5th cavalry 1st cav
div on the
border of saudi arabia and iraq in 1991,i was on a roving
guard duty alone within a perimeter.Towards the end of my one hour
shift,i went and sat down.To my left and south i
saw an irridescent light that appeared to change colors as
rapidly as you can imagine,until it was a blur of colors.
as it approached,and began to pass behind me,i struck my
cigarrette lighter on high and held it up in the air.The
craft began to pan around me at my left side until it was
directly in front of me.It was twenty feet off of the ground
and thirty feet forward of me.It was silent and there was no
rotor wash,which a helicopter would give off.It was archaic
looking,discoidal in shape,had a cupola on top,a beacon on
the bottom,which it had instantaneosly turned off when i had
lit my lighter.The sky was completely clear.All aircraft
flying towards iraq were above twenty thousand feet and were
observing light discipline.The discoidal craft had leading
edges that were flattened out and scored.The craft gave off
a field of palpable energy.I had with me a loaded m-16,a
set of night-vision goggles,a pr-77 radio telephone to
communicate with the command post,and an unloaded m-60
strapped to my back.I felt no fear,indeed the opposite was
true.All i could do was outstretch my arm strenously.I felt
as if i were hypnotized.The craft began to oscillate faster
and faster like a gyroscope until it came to rest, showing
it s underside.A pattern of lights emerged.First was three
pinpoints in the shape of a triangle.Then four pinpoints in
the shape of a rectangle.Then one point of light that out-
stretched itself into a long line of light.All i can remember next
is the craft moving north and finding myself
walking towards our gp large(tent).My guard duty was supposed to
have ended at 12 midnight,but my watch showed it
to be 1:30.I had lost time.I entered the tent and woke up
the next guard who was impossible to awake.I had to drag him
outside,and set him on a picnic table.I re-entered the tent
and laid down on my cot and got into my sleeping bag since
the desert nights are cold.Maybe one minute later the entire
tent erupted into chaos.Private first class **** *********
was being choked in his sleep by specialist ***** ******.The
rest of the personnel were waving m-16 s around and flashlights
were playing on the walls of the tent.Personnel
were screaming.It was as if everyone had been suddenly
released from suspended hypnotism or something.Weird.I don t
know if that craft was an air force or navy aerial platform
or not,but whatever it was it was awesome.
timothy alec sisson
100% service-connected disabled

Sighting report:   i am wondering if there was any kind of unusual
aircraft testing going on may 21, 2005? my husband and i were at the
drive-in, preparing to watch (the irony of it) star wars iii.  it
was around 8:45 pm or so,with a clear evening sky, and the first
sign we had was of what looked like a bright white light. my husband
pointed it out, and thought it might be a weather balloon. a few
minutes later, in approximately the same spot, i saw an extremely
bright light, only it looked like a burst of light or flame. then,
from that initial light, came a stream of smoke or vapor, which then
led to a second light which seemed to be on fire. from that second
light, then came a stream of smoke or vapor, leading to a third
light. i have never seen a separation of rocket stages in person,
but from videos i have seen, that is the closest description that i
can give. only this was no where near a space center. this took
place above the horizon in the west/southwest and lasted about 30
seconds altogether. we do have an air force base on our town
outskirts, but this is not anything like their normal flight
patterns or aircraft. i would love to know if anyone else saw
something similar?

Sighting report:   this is not my sighting but my brothers and a
couple of other friends. the year was 2001 and my brother was
throwing a big party for his son s (my nephew)1st birthday. i was
working at speedzone at the time and he had invited me and i had the
feeling that something special was going to happen. unfortunately i
had to work so i couldn t go. so at the party my brother and a
couple of friends (8 of them ) were having a good time eating,
drinking, and celebrating. but later on in the night after the party
was over, most of them were to drunk to drive home so they spent the
night over. at about 4:30-5:00 in the morning, one of his friends
got thirsty and went to the kitchen to get something to drink. my
brother had a house that had a big field and a high school football
stadium in his backyard and you could see all this through his
kitchen. and when he turned around he saw something that he knew was
not a plane. so he woke everyone up and they all ran to the
backyard. what they saw was a strange egg shaped object that looked
like it was floating on water. it had windows and bars that ran
across it like an "x". every now and then then object would spin and
when it did, it would shine of a light but the light would only go
so far so it looked more like a forcefield. they all watched in
amazement as this object hovered and they were all hypnotized by it
and all though there were plenty of cameras in the house, no one
wanted to go inside because they wanted to see what it would do
next. then out of the right side, they saw what they thought was a
plane but the light dimmed out when it got close to the u.F.O and
reappeared, but when it reappeared it turned from one big light to
alot of little "globes" with what looked like mist around it. then
they saw they "globes" go inside the u.F.O and the u.F.O stayed
around for an extra 5 minutes before leaving. the next day when my
brother told me about it i didn t believe him because i was always

Sighting report:   we were driving past the high school and looked
up to see a light near the olmos park area.  we followed it to olmos
park.  when we got out, it was about 9:00 p.M., it had been dark for
about an hour, so it was hard to see anything except a bright
illuminated outline of a creature in the park.  we got out to
inspect the situation.  there were a few other men with flashlights
who helped.  then the figure disappeared, like faded. uh, what
should i do?  i m not sure who to call.  there were some bent bushes
and alot of witnesses in the park, but i m not sure how reliable
they ll be.

Sighting report:   tuesday march 22nd. bike riding i was in a
 large field used for jogging and biking. i had gone out to
 document the various types of con-trails. there was a light haze
 in the sky caused by the con-trails. looking staight up i
 witnessed a silvery ball of light moving accross the sky from
 the southeast to the northwest. the wind that day was from the
 northwest and headed toward the southeast. i fixed my digital
 video camera on the object and for three minutes i caught the
 image on film. it had a steady pace and seemed to move in a
 straight line toward the end of the sighting the object stopped
 moving. at this point i panned over to another part ofd the sky
 of a second and when i returned the object was gone. later i
 went back and viewed the tape. a week later when i took the time
 to look at the rest of the tape of the con-trails i found
 another completely different object in another part of the sky
 at the same time. this object was captured by complete accident
 and was not seen until later. this object was in the far north
 horizon and appears to be of oval shape and bright sliver in
 color. i have downloaded this onto my computer yet i am still
 learning how to operate the digital video programs. i am willing
 to share this with you all if you would like. please let me know
 and if you may have any questions feel free to contact me at my
 e-mail or telephone.
-thank you for your attention, rene.
